 5. LNNVL

Used in WHERE clause when condition contains NULL.

Example

```sql
SELECT *
FROM employees
WHERE LNNVL(salary > 5000);
Employees:
| EMP_ID | NAME  | SALARY |
| ------ | ----- | ------ |
| 101    | Ravi  | 60000  |
| 102    | Meena | 45000  |
| 103    | Arjun | 70000  |
| 104    | Priya | 40000  |
| 105    | Kiran | NULL   |

SELECT emp_id, name, salary
FROM employees
WHERE LNNVL(salary > 50000);
| EMP_ID | NAME  | SALARY |
| ------ | ----- | ------ |
| 102    | Meena | 45000  |
| 104    | Priya | 40000  |
| 105    | Kiran | NULL   |

Returns rows where condition is false or NULL.
2. Numeric Functions
1. ABS
Returns absolute value.

```sql
SELECT ABS(-15) FROM dual;
Output
15

2. CEIL
Returns next highest integer.

```sql
SELECT CEIL(5.2) FROM dual;
```
Output

```
6

3. FLOOR
Returns largest integer less than or equal.

```sql
SELECT FLOOR(5.9) FROM dual;
```

Output

```
5
```

 4. MOD
Returns remainder.
```sql
SELECT MOD(10,3) FROM dual;
Output

```
1

5. POWER

Returns number raised to power.

```sql
SELECT POWER(2,3) FROM dual;
```

Output
8

6. REMAINDER
Another remainder function.

```sql
SELECT REMAINDER(10,3) FROM dual;
```
7. ROUND

Rounds number.
```sql
