 🔷 3. Conditional Functions

✅ 1. DECODE (Oracle only)

Works like IF-ELSE

 Syntax

```sql
DECODE(column, value1, result1, 
               value2, result2, default)
 Example

```sql
SELECT DECODE(dept_id,
              10, 'HR',
              20, 'IT',
              30, 'Finance',
              'Other') AS department
FROM employees;
 Output

| dept_id | department |
| ------- | ---------- |
| 10      | HR         |
| 20      | IT         |
| 40      | Other      |


* Mapping codes to values (very common in DB)


#✅ 2. CASE (Standard SQL – Most Important)

More flexible than DECODE.

---

 🔹 Simple CASE

```sql
SELECT 
  CASE dept_id
    WHEN 10 THEN 'HR'
    WHEN 20 THEN 'IT'
    ELSE 'Other'
  END AS department
FROM employees;
 
🔹 Searched CASE (Most Used)

```sql
SELECT 
  name,
  salary,
  CASE 
    WHEN salary > 5000 THEN 'High'
    WHEN salary BETWEEN 3000 AND 5000 THEN 'Medium'
    ELSE 'Low'
  END AS salary_category
FROM employees;
 Output

| name | salary | category |
| ---- | ------ | -------- |
| John | 6000   | High     |
| Sam  | 4000   | Medium   |
| Raj  | 2000   | Low      |

